          "ambient",
          "0.1"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "A corridor leading toward the library, lined with glass-fronted cases of journals and bound reports. Clean north light through tall windows.\n\nShe stops in front of a case of geological survey reports. One catches her: *Metropolitan Railway Subterranean Survey, 1860. Preliminary Findings.* The spine is uncracked. No one has opened it since it was shelved."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
