          "ambient",
          "0.2"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "A rented room in a terraced house near Fitzrovia. Plain walls, a table, two chairs, a window with the curtain half-drawn. The kind of room that has housed many temporary arrangements without accumulating any permanent character.\n\nThe woman at the table has no name that Ida has been given. She handles the more complex Quill operations. She looks at Ida with the specific attention of someone assessing a tool's condition."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
