          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:receiver-default"
        ],
        [
          "requires",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:quest:quill-job-5",
          "active",
          ""
        ]
      ],
      "content": "The package ends here \u2014 at a man in the Lamb and Flag on Edgware Road. He takes it without acknowledgement, pockets it, returns to his drink.\n\nHe has a Smithfield accent. He is the third hand. He is also someone Rook knows by name."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-default"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "I have an appointment.",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:voss-appointment"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "I was sent by the Quill.",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:voss-quill"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He looks up from the desk. A brief professional assessment \u2014 patient or not patient \u2014 and then the practised neutrality settles over his face.\n\n*Yes?* he says."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-appointment"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He checks a book on the desk. Finds nothing. Looks at her.\n\n*There's no appointment under your name.* He returns to his papers. The conversation is over, as far as he is concerned."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-quill"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "Something shifts. Not alarm \u2014 he is too practised for that \u2014 but a recalibration. He puts down the pen.\n\n*What do you need?* The professional warmth has gone and what remains is more honest: careful, watchful, slightly tired.\n\nHe has been waiting for someone to come."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-uneasy"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "What do you know about Harwick?",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:voss-harwick"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "What does the Quill ask of you?",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:voss-quill-asks"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He looks at Ida with the particular attention of someone who has worked out that the girl running errands is more observant than errands require.\n\n*You've been doing this a while*, he says. It contains something almost like relief \u2014 as though someone paying attention is, in itself, useful."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-harwick"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He is quiet for a moment.\n\n*Harwick engaged this practice three years ago*, he says. *To certify certain individuals. Certify them as \u2014 unsuitable to manage their own affairs.* He looks at the locked filing cabinet. *The individuals were not unsuitable. They were inconvenient.*\n\nHe stops. His hands are flat on the desk. *I signed the papers*, he says. *That is what I know about Harwick.*"
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-quill-asks"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "*Information*, he says. *Medical information about people whose health it would be useful to know about. Occasionally a certification.* He pauses. *I told myself it was a small part of what I do.*\n\nHe looks at her steadily.\n\n*I'm not sure I believe that anymore.*"
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-candid"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "What's in the locked cabinet?",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:voss-cabinet"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "The Quill is using you.",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:voss-using"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He does not bother with the professional manner when she comes in for the third time.\n\n*You've found the money*, he says. *Where it goes.* Not a question. *Which means you know more than Fenn intended you to.*\n\nSomething has resolved in him \u2014 not peace, but a decision."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-cabinet"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ],
        [
          "on-enter",
          "player",
          "",
          "set-state",
          "visible",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:clue:voss-records"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "*Names*, he says. *People I certified. My real assessments \u2014 before the Quill's version was written over them.* He looks at the cabinet. *I kept them. I don't know why. Some remnant of a principle I had.*\n\nHe takes a key from his waistcoat pocket and places it on the desk between them. He does not push it toward her.\n\n*I can't use them myself*, he says. *If someone else could\u2014* He doesn't finish."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:voss-using"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "*Yes*, he says. Simply.\n\n*And so are you*, he says. *The difference is you know it.* He pauses. *That's more than I managed for the first two years.*\n\nIt is not unkind. It is the most honest thing anyone has said to her in months."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:handler-default"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "Fenn sent me.",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:handler-fenn"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "She looks at Ida without expression. Waiting."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:handler-fenn"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "*I know*, she says. *He told me you were thorough.* Not a compliment or a criticism \u2014 purely information. *Sit down.*\n\nShe tells Ida about the blackmail money. Three hands, three journeys. The Quill wants to know where it ends. Not to stop it \u2014 to know. Knowledge is the only currency that compounds."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:handler-job5"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "It ends at the Lamb and Flag, Edgware Road.",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:handler-report"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "I'm still watching.",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:handler-still-watching"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "She looks up when Ida comes back.\n\n*Well?* she says."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
