          "",
          "set-state",
          "complete",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:quest:quill-job-5"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "The handler writes it down. Three lines. She underlines something.\n\n*The Lamb and Flag*, she says. *That's Shambles territory.* She looks at Ida steadily. *Which means someone in the Shambles is blackmailing a Quill clerk. Which means\u2014*\n\n*The factions are already touching each other*, Ida says.\n\nThe handler looks at her for a long moment. *Yes*, she says. *They are.*"
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:handler-still-watching"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "*Come back when you have it*, the handler says. She closes the notebook. The meeting is over."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:student-default"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He looks up briefly from the stack of books. *Sorry \u2014 do you need to get past?* He moves aside without waiting for an answer, already back in whatever he was thinking about."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:student-notebook"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "Return the notebook.",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:student-returned"
        ],
        [
          "option",
          "Keep it.",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:dialogue:student-kept"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He stops when she holds it up. His face goes through three expressions: confusion, recognition, relief.\n\n*That's mine. I've been looking \u2014 where did you\u2014*\n\nHe reaches for it."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:student-returned"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ],
        [
          "on-enter",
          "player",
          "",
          "consume-item",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:item:ucl-notebook"
        ],
        [
          "on-enter",
          "player",
          "",
          "set-state",
          "complete",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:metropolitan:quest:side-ucl-notebook"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "She gives it back. He takes it with both hands.\n\n*Thank you. These are my field notes \u2014 the railway geology survey. I'd have had to redo the whole thing.* He looks at her with sudden curiosity. *Are you a student here?*\n\nShe says no. He accepts this without judgment and tucks the notebook under his arm. *Well. Thank you*, he says again, and walks away.\n\nHe will not remember her face. She is used to this."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:student-kept"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "She says she found nothing. He frowns and sighs. *Must have left it in the library*, he says, and turns back.\n\nThe notebook is in Ida's pocket. Dense with observations about what the railway tunnellers found underground \u2014 geological notes, sketches, a reference to an unexplained chamber near King's Cross that was sealed and not recorded in the official survey.\n\nThis will matter later."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:carrier-1-default"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He does not look at Ida. He watches the tunnel mouth and waits for Baker Street. The package shifts slightly under his arm when the carriage jolts. He steadies it."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:carrier-2-default"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "She boards at Baker Street from the opposite end of the platform. She does not acknowledge the first man. The package is in the basket, beneath a cloth. She sits. She looks out the window. She is entirely ordinary."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "metropolitan:dialogue:receiver-default"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "metropolitan"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "dialogue"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "He takes the basket from the woman at the Lamb and Flag with the ease of a regular transaction. He lifts the cloth, removes the package, tucks it away. He hands the basket back.\n\nHe has a Smithfield accent. He orders another drink without looking at anyone. The money ends here."
    },
    {
